<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Search Term Formats</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/5.15.3/css/all.min.css">
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #121212;
      color: #fff;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 600px;
      margin-top: 100px;
    }
    h2 {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      color: #fff;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      color: #fff;
    }
    a {
      color: #007bff;
    }
    a:hover {
      color: #0069d9;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="mb-4">Search Term Formats</h2>
    <p>To perform advanced searches, you can use search terms in the following formats:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Field Name: Exact Value</strong> - Search for records where the specified field has an exact value.</li>
      <li><strong>Field Name: Partial Value</strong> - Search for records where the specified field contains a partial value.</li>
      <li><strong>Field Name: "Quoted Value"</strong> - Search for records where the specified field has an exact value enclosed in quotes.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For example:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>firstName: John</code> - Search for records where the first name is exactly "John".</li>
      <li><code>lastName: Smith</code> - Search for records where the last name contains the value "Smith".</li>
      <li><code>city: "New York"</code> - Search for records where the city is exactly "New York".</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Feel free to experiment with different search term formats to refine your search results.</p>
    <p><a href="/search">Go back to search</a></p>
  </div>
  <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/your-font-awesome-kit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
